# call.word — the CALL verb, the do that wakes a being to act. Was summon.
# Descends from word.word, do.word, being.word, name.word. A do may act on a being as a body
# (do move, do set); that is no call. A call rouses the being to act as itself, through a Name
# that can act through it (its own, or an inhabitor). The host (seed/ibp/verbs/call.js) delivers
# the said to the being's stance and wakes its scheduler. The inbox is a view on its stamp.
# `wake` is grounded here. The said is the inner-Word, shown in quotes. The call is the Word.

A call is a do that wakes a being, that a Name may act through it.
A do may move or set a being's body, and is no call. A call wakes the being itself, that its Name may act through it.
A call makes the world after twice. Once when it is made, the ask. Once more when the being wakes to its own moment, and a Name acts through it.
A call has a said, what the caller speaks to it.
A call may have an intent, the why behind the said.
A call may be in reply to a call before it.
A being's inbox is its calls not yet seen.
By its cognition, the being sees its calls, and its Name replies.
A reply is a call back.
